cz.melkamar.andruian.viewlink.ui.main

Class MapViewPort

  • java.lang.Object
    • cz.melkamar.andruian.viewlink.ui.main.MapViewPort

  • public class MapViewPort
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing a viewport of the map. It is described by its bounding box, the bottom leftmost coordinate (sw) and the top rightmost coordinate (ne).

    • Constructor Detail

      • MapViewPort

        public MapViewPort(com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng northeast,
                   com.google.android.gms.maps.model.LatLng southwest)
        Create a MapViewPort with "normalized" boundaries, where the left edge always has a lower longitude than the right edge. It does not "wrap around" like regular latlng does.

        If the left edge of the viewport is higher number than the right edge, it means it overflowed. To fix that, add 360 to the right edge so that it appears on the right side of the left edge.

        Parameters:
        northeast -
        southwest -
